Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.30,0:54:22.30,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,He is unharmed.\N{\rCHT}他毫髮無損{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.30,0:54:25.27,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,I've spoken with your husband about his survival.\N{\rCHT}我跟你丈夫談過他的倖存{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.30,0:54:28.03,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,l suggested a rather unbelievable possibility.\N{\rCHT}我告訴他一個可能性{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.31,0:54:29.57,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Since then,\N{\rCHT}從那時起{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.81,0:54:33.74,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,I've come to believe that possibility,\N{\rCHT}我就相信那個可能性{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.81,0:54:36.25,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,however unbelievable, is now more aprobability.\N{\rCHT}現在它可更有可能了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.32,0:54:39.25,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,And what was it you suggested?\N{\rCHT}你告訴他什麼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.32,0:54:41.82,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,These are mediocre times, Mrs Dunn.\N{\rCHT}這是個平凡的時代 鄧太太{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.82,0:54:43.27,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,People a restarting to lose hope.\N{\rCHT}人們失去希望{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.27,0:54:45.69,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,it's hard for many to believe\N{\rCHT}許多人不信...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.82,0:54:47.76,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,there are extraordinary things inside themselves\N{\rCHT}他們自己有不凡之處{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.76,0:54:49.49,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,as Well as others.\N{\rCHT}跟其他人一樣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.83,0:54:52.73,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,l hope you can keep an open mind.\N{\rCHT}希望你能敞開心胸{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.87,0:55:36.60,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Excuse me, sir?\N{\rCHT}抱歉{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.38,0:55:39.74,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Can you step out of line, please?\N{\rCHT}請你出來一下{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.14,0:55:45.31,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,We've been having some problems\N{\rCHT}我們有些問題{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.44,0:55:47.89,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,with people selling drugs here in the stadium.\N{\rCHT}關於體育場裡毒品交易{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.89,0:55:50.88,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Would you mind if l check your pockets?\N{\rCHT}不介意我檢查你的口袋吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.39,0:55:53.38,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Raise your arms, please.\N{\rCHT}請把手舉起來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.39,0:55:56.29,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Come on, raise them up.\N{\rCHT}快 舉起來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.90,0:55:58.89,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,l just got here, man.\N{\rCHT}我才剛到這裡{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.41,0:56:11.77,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Can l put my hands down now?\N{\rCHT}能把手放下了嗎{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.42,0:56:19.32,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Can l go?\N{\rCHT}可以走了吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.42,0:56:22.05,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Yeah.\N{\rCHT}可以{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.92,0:56:26.39,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Hope you find them.\N{\rCHT}真希望你找到什麼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.93,0:56:36.49,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Yo, Dunn.\N{\rCHT}小鄧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.94,0:56:39.06,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Yeah.\N{\rCHT}請說{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.44,0:56:40.68,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,l just came into the office.\N{\rCHT}我剛到辦公室{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.68,0:56:42.34,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Your kid Was hurt.\N{\rCHT}你小孩受傷了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.94,0:56:45.34,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Where is he?\N{\rCHT}他在哪裡{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.44,0:56:46.39,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Some play Rehearsal at school.\N{\rCHT}在學校{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.40,0:56:49.24,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,He Wants you to come down there.\N{\rCHT}他要你立刻過去{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.63,0:57:05.49,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Is that your dad?\N{\rCHT}那是你爸{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.63,0:57:13.16,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,l bet my dad could beat up your dad.\N{\rCHT}我敢賭我爸一定能打贏你爸{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.14,0:57:19.14,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,No. He, uh... he insisted we call only you,\N{\rCHT}不 他堅持我們只通知你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.14,0:57:21.37,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,though we had some trouble tracking you down.\N{\rCHT}雖然你很難找{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.65,0:57:24.65,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,l mean, you're not on our list.\N{\rCHT}資料上沒寫你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.65,0:57:26.34,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Audrey handles this type of stuff.\N{\rCHT}這類的事都由奧莉處理{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.65,0:57:29.95,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Oh. What type of stuff?\N{\rCHT}哪類的事{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.66,0:57:32.92,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,joseph stuff.\N{\rCHT}喬瑟的事{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.66,0:57:38.06,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Do l need to put any smelly ointment on him or anything?\N{\rCHT}我需要幫他敷藥嗎{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.16,0:57:40.86,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,No, no. it's more emotional damage\N{\rCHT}不用 他心靈上的創傷較重{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.17,0:57:43.90,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,not, not too serious, physically.\N{\rCHT}身體上的傷不重{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.17,0:57:48.16,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Nothing like when l sent you to the hospital.\N{\rCHT}不像以前我送你就醫一樣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.68,0:57:53.68,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,When was that?\N{\rCHT}什麼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.68,0:57:59.08,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,My office was on the other side of the building back then.\N{\rCHT}我的辦公室以前在另一邊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.69,0:58:03.85,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,You don't remember me, do you?\N{\rCHT}你不記得我了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.69,0:58:07.16,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,No, ma'am.\N{\rCHT}不記得{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.19,0:58:10.22,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,l had red hair.\N{\rCHT}我以前一頭紅發{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.20,0:58:16.70,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Well, you Were a little younger than Joseph When it happened.\N{\rCHT}事故發生當時你比喬瑟還小{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.70,0:58:18.36,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Did you know that we changed\N{\rCHT}知道嗎...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.70,0:58:24.07,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,the rules of conduct around the pool because of you?\N{\rCHT}我們因你改變泳池活動規則{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.71,0:58:27.47,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,The kids Still tell about it\N{\rCHT}孩子們現在還在議論{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.71,0:58:31.22,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,like it Was some sort of ghost story.\N{\rCHT}把它當成像鬼故事一樣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.22,0:58:35.81,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Did you know there Was a kid nearly drowned in that pool?\N{\rCHT}你知道泳池裡差點淹死人嗎{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.72,0:58:39.95,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,He lay on the bottom Of the pool for 5 minutes,\N{\rCHT}他沉在池底五分鐘{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.23,0:58:42.69,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,and When they pulled him out,\N{\rCHT}他被撈出來時{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.73,0:58:45.16,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,he Was dead.\N{\rCHT}他已經死了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.23,0:58:51.19,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,We let them tell it.\N{\rCHT}我們隨他們講{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.19,0:58:53.80,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,lt help skeep them safe.\N{\rCHT}注意安全就好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.74,0:59:00.14,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,You still phobic Of Water?\N{\rCHT}你還怕水嗎{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.25,0:59:04.37,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,it Was Potter And another guy.\N{\rCHT}是波特和另一個人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.75,0:59:09.45,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,They Were messing With this Chinese girl in the dressing room.\N{\rCHT}他們在更衣室捉弄一個女生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.75,0:59:13.55,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,You can't let Bad things happen to good people, right?\N{\rCHT}你不喜歡好人遇上壞事 對吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.26,0:59:18.25,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,That's your code, right? That's the hero's code.\N{\rCHT}那是你的天性 英雄的天性{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.26,0:59:21.16,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,l tried to make them stop,\N{\rCHT}我想叫他們住手{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.27,0:59:23.38,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,but they kept pushing me down,\N{\rCHT}但他們把我推下{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.38,0:59:25.50,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,and they wouldn't let me get back up.\N{\rCHT}不讓我起來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.27,0:59:31.71,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,l thought maybe because you're my dad...\N{\rCHT}我想也許因為你是我爸{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.28,0:59:35.37,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,l thought l might be like you.\N{\rCHT}我可能也會像你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.78,0:59:39.88,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,I'm not like you.\N{\rCHT}我不像你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.79,0:59:44.41,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,You are like me.\N{\rCHT}你像我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.29,0:59:48.29,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,We can both get hurt.\N{\rCHT}我們都會受傷{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.29,0:59:50.06,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,l'm just an ordinary man.\N{\rCHT}我只是普通人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.30,0:59:53.13,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,No, you're not.\N{\rCHT}你不是{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.30,0:59:57.00,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Why do you keep saying that?\N{\rCHT}你為什麼一直那麼說{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.64,1:00:06.98,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Eliijah Price came to visit me at the centre today.\N{\rCHT}普伊萊今天到複健中心找我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.15,1:00:10.17,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,jesus.\N{\rCHT}天啊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.15,1:00:13.65,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,He didn't do anything. He just...\N{\rCHT}他沒做什麼 只是...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.65,1:00:16.12,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,told me his theory.\N{\rCHT}跟我說他的理論{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.16,1:00:19.66,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,That's sad, when patients get like that.\N{\rCHT}病人變成這樣真是悲哀{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.66,1:00:22.22,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,They lose reality.\N{\rCHT}神智不清{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.67,1:00:29.13,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Joseph, what the hell are you doing?\N{\rCHT}喬瑟 你這是幹嘛{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.17,1:00:30.79,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Oh, my God.\N{\rCHT}天啊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.67,1:00:35.13,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,You don't believe. I'll show you. You can't get hurt.\N{\rCHT}你不相信 你不會受傷的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.17,1:00:38.14,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,That gun's not loaded. He doesn't know where l keep the bullets.\N{\rCHT}那沒上膛 他不知道子彈放哪{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.18,1:00:41.30,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,ln your Rookie of the Year trophy.\N{\rCHT}在你的新人獎獎盃裡{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.68,1:00:44.18,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Joseph, did you load that gun?\N{\rCHT}喬瑟 你上膛了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.18,1:00:45.68,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,You won't get hurt.\N{\rCHT}你不會受傷的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.68,1:00:47.81,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Eliijah Was Wrong.\N{\rCHT}伊萊錯了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.19,1:00:49.18,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,When did he meet Eliijah?\N{\rCHT}他怎麼會見過伊萊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.19,1:00:50.45,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,He was with me when l met him.\N{\rCHT}跟我一起去見的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.69,1:00:52.69,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,No one believes him.\N{\rCHT}沒人相信他{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.69,1:00:55.19,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,joseph, listen to me.\N{\rCHT}喬瑟 聽我說{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.19,1:00:59.36,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Sometimes when people get sick or hurt\N{\rCHT}有時人們生病或受傷太久{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.70,1:01:00.82,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,for a long time, like Elijah,\N{\rCHT}就像伊萊...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.20,1:01:03.24,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,their mind gets hurt, too,\N{\rCHT}他們心靈也病了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.24,1:01:04.70,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,and they start to think things, that aren't true.\N{\rCHT}會妄想{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.70,1:01:06.46,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,He told me what he thought about your father.\N{\rCHT}他跟我談你爸{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.46,1:01:08.50,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,it isn't true.\N{\rCHT}那不是真的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.71,1:01:10.90,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,I'll show you.\N{\rCHT}我讓你見識見識{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.71,1:01:15.68,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Do you remember the story about,\N{\rCHT}記得那個差點{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.68,1:01:17.65,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,about the boy that almost drowned in the pool?\N{\rCHT}淹死的小孩吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.72,1:01:18.81,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,That was me they were talking about.\N{\rCHT}他們說的是我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.81,1:01:20.08,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,l almost died. That was me.\N{\rCHT}我差點淹死{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.22,1:01:21.78,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,- You're lying. - I'm not lying, okay?\N{\rCHT}- 你說謊 - 我沒有{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.78,1:01:22.88,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,l just didn't remember it, that's all.\N{\rCHT}我只是忘了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.22,1:01:24.90,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Joseph, you know your father was injured in college.\N{\rCHT}你爸大學時受過傷{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.90,1:01:29.16,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,You know that. You know all about that.\N{\rCHT}你知道的 你很清楚{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.23,1:01:31.72,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Don't do it. He'll die, Joseph.\N{\rCHT}別開槍 他會死的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.23,1:01:33.23,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,I'll just shoot him once.\N{\rCHT}我只射他一槍{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.23,1:01:35.70,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,joseph, listen to what your mot\N{\rCHT}喬瑟 聽你媽...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.74,1:01:39.26,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Don't be scared.\N{\rCHT}不要怕{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.24,1:01:44.73,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,if you pull that trigger, I'm going to leave.\N{\rCHT}你要是扣板機 我就搬走{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.74,1:01:47.77,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Do you understand? l'm going to go to New York.\N{\rCHT}懂嗎 我要去紐約{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.25,1:01:50.15,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,You're right.\N{\rCHT}沒錯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.25,1:01:53.22,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Lf you pull that trigger, that bullet is just going to bounce off me,\N{\rCHT}如果你開槍 子彈還是會從我身上彈開{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.25,1:01:54.75,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,and I'm not going to be hurt,\N{\rCHT}我不會受傷{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.75,1:01:57.05,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,but then I'm going to go upstairs\N{\rCHT}但我接著會上樓去拿行李{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.26,1:02:00.66,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,and I'm going to pack and I'm going to leave for New York.\N{\rCHT}動身前往紐約{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.76,1:02:01.26,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Why?\N{\rCHT}為什麼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.26,1:02:04.14,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,Because l thought We Were just starting\N{\rCHT}因為我以為我們是{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.14,1:02:05.22,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,to be friends for real,\N{\rCHT}好朋友{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.76,1:02:06.77,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,and friends will listen to each other.\N{\rCHT}朋友會聽彼此的話{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.77,1:02:11.23,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,And they don't shoot each other, do they, Audrey?\N{\rCHT}他們不互相傷害 對吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.77,1:02:14.77,ENG,NTP,0,0,0,!Effect,No shooting friends, joseph.\N{\rCHT}不能傷害朋友 喬瑟{\r}
